<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Faction hits for looting PvE kills</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:49 p.m. 19/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Faction hits for looting PvE kills<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1072" TARGET=_self>One other thought...</A> (Ndaven)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Yeah, I know, it's a touchy subject, BUT... Wouldn't it make

<BR>&gt; sense to have looting effect faction standing as well? So if you
<BR>&gt; go around looting bodies you haven't killed, you will still take
<BR>&gt; hits? It *could* even have an RP basis - if you took seperate
<BR>&gt; hits for killing and looting, you could play a nobler character
<BR>&gt; who will kill but not steal from the dead.. actions like that
<BR>&gt; would be more respected, so you wouldn't become AS hated.. :)
<P>It's an interesting idea. As a roleplayer, I don't like it because it feels artifical. As a powergamer, I don't like it because... well, because it would stop me from taking advantage of other people's mistakes.
<P>But my personal feelings aside, it probably wouldn't hurt anything. I would only like to add that if such a system were put in place, it should be in addition to the current faction hit. So if you killed a player, you'd take a hit. If you loot the kill, you'd take ANOTHER hit. Making each one half as bad would give newbie killers twice as long to run rampant before they destroy their ratings.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
